.TH rift-cli 1  "rift-cli " "rift-cli manual"
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH NAME
rift\-cli \- Command\-line interface for rift window manager
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrift\-cli\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH DESCRIPTION
Command\-line interface for rift window manager
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH OPTIONS
Command\-line interface for rift window manager
.TP
\fBUsage: rift\-cli <COMMAND>\fR
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH "SUBCOMMAND: rift-cli query"
Query information from rift
.TP
\fBUsage: rift\-cli query <COMMAND>\fR
.PP
\fBCommands:\fR
.TP
\fBrift\-cli query workspaces [\-\-space\-id]\fR
List virtual workspaces (optionally for a specific MacOS space)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli query windows [\-\-space\-id]\fR
List windows (optionally filtered by space)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli query displays\fR
List connected displays
.TP
\fBrift\-cli query window <WINDOW_ID>\fR
Get information about a specific window
.TP
\fBrift\-cli query applications\fR
List running applications
.TP
\fBrift\-cli query layout <SPACE_ID>\fR
Get layout state for a space
.TP
\fBrift\-cli query workspace\-layout [\-\-space\-id] [\-\-workspace\-id]\fR
Get workspace layout\-engine mode(s)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli query metrics\fR
Get performance metrics
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH "SUBCOMMAND: rift-cli execute"
Execute commands in rift
.TP
\fBUsage: rift\-cli execute <COMMAND>\fR
.PP
\fBCommands:\fR
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute window next\fR
Focus the next window
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute window prev\fR
Focus the previous window
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute window focus <DIRECTION>\fR
Move focus in a direction
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute window toggle\-float\fR
Toggle window floating state
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute window toggle\-fullscreen\fR
Toggle fullscreen mode (fills the whole screen, ignores outer gaps)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute window toggle\-fullscreen\-within\-gaps\fR
Toggle fullscreen within configured outer gaps (respects outer gaps / fills tiling area)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute window resize\-grow\fR
Grow the current window size (increments by ~5%)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute window resize\-shrink\fR
Shrink the current window size (decrements by ~5%)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute window resize\-by <AMOUNT>\fR
Resize the selected window by a fractional amount. \- Pass a signed floating value: positive to grow, negative to shrink. \- The value is a fraction of the current size (e.g. `0.05` = 5%). Examples: rift\-cli execute window resize\-by \-\-amount 0.05    # grow by 5% rift\-cli execute window resize\-by \-\-amount \-0.10   # shrink by 10%
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute window close \-\-window\-id <WINDOW_ID>\fR
Close a window by window server identifier
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute window add\-scratchpad\fR
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute window toggle\-scratchpad [\-\-name]\fR
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute workspace next [SKIP_EMPTY]\fR
Switch to next workspace
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute workspace prev [SKIP_EMPTY]\fR
Switch to previous workspace
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute workspace switch <WORKSPACE_ID>\fR
Switch to specific workspace
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute workspace move\-window <WORKSPACE_ID> [WINDOW_ID]\fR
Move current window to workspace
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute workspace create\fR
Create a new workspace
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute workspace last\fR
Switch to the last workspace
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute workspace set\-layout [\-\-workspace\-id] <MODE>\fR
Set layout mode for a workspace (or active workspace when omitted)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute layout ascend\fR
Move selection up the tree
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute layout descend\fR
Move selection down the tree
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute layout move\-node <DIRECTION>\fR
Move the selected node in a direction
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute layout join\-window <DIRECTION>\fR
Join the selected window with neighbor in a direction
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute layout toggle\-stack\fR
Toggle stacked state for the selected container
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute layout toggle\-orientation\fR
Global orientation toggle that works consistently across layout modes (and between splits/stacks)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute layout unjoin\fR
Unjoin previously joined windows
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute layout toggle\-focus\-float\fR
Toggle floating on the focused selection (tree focus)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute layout adjust\-master\-ratio <DELTA>\fR
Adjust master ratio by a delta (master/stack layout only)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute layout adjust\-master\-count <DELTA>\fR
Adjust master count by a delta (master/stack layout only)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute layout promote\-to\-master\fR
Promote the selected window into the master area (master/stack layout only)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute layout swap\-master\-stack\fR
Swap the first master with the first stack window (master/stack layout only)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute layout swap\-windows <A> <B>\fR
Swap two windows by window id (`WindowId { pid: ..., idx: ... }`)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute layout scroll\-strip <DELTA>\fR
Scroll the strip by a normalized delta (scrolling layout only)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute layout snap\-strip\fR
Snap the strip to the nearest column boundary (scrolling layout only)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute layout center\-selection\fR
Toggle centering of the selected column in scrolling layout. If invoked again on the same selection, centering is removed
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute config set\-animate <VALUE>\fR
Update animation settings
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute config set\-animation\-duration <VALUE>\fR
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute config set\-animation\-fps <VALUE>\fR
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute config set\-animation\-easing <VALUE>\fR
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute config set\-mouse\-follows\-focus <VALUE>\fR
Update mouse settings
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute config set\-mouse\-hides\-on\-focus <VALUE>\fR
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute config set\-focus\-follows\-mouse <VALUE>\fR
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute config set\-stack\-offset <VALUE>\fR
Update layout settings
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute config set\-stack\-default\-orientation <VALUE>\fR
Set the default stack orientation behavior. Value should be one of: "perpendicular", "same", "horizontal", or "vertical"
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute config set\-outer\-gaps <TOP> <LEFT> <BOTTOM> <RIGHT>\fR
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute config set\-inner\-gaps <HORIZONTAL> <VERTICAL>\fR
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute config set\-workspace\-names [NAMES]\fR
Update workspace settings
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute config set <KEY> <VALUE>\fR
Generic set: set an arbitrary config key (dot\-separated path) to a JSON value. Example: rift\-cli execute config set \-\-key settings.animate \-\-value true
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute config get\fR
Get current config
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute config save\fR
Save current config to file
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute config reload\fR
Reload config from file
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute mission\-control show\-all\fR
Show all workspaces in mission control
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute mission\-control show\-current\fR
Show current workspace in mission control
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute mission\-control dismiss\fR
Dismiss mission control
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute display focus [\-\-direction] [\-\-index] [\-\-uuid]\fR
Focus a display by direction, index, or UUID
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute display move\-mouse\-to\-index <INDEX>\fR
Move mouse cursor to a display by index (0\-based)
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute display move\-mouse\-to\-uuid <UUID>\fR
Move mouse cursor to a display by UUID
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute display move\-window [\-\-direction] [\-\-index] [\-\-uuid] [\-\-window\-id]\fR
Move a window to a display by direction, index, or UUID
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute save\-and\-exit\fR
Save current state and exit rift
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute debug\fR
Print layout tree debugging output in the running rift instance
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute serialize\fR
Serialize and print runtime state
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute toggle\-space\-activated\fR
Toggle whether the current space is managed by rift
.TP
\fBrift\-cli execute show\-timing\fR
Show timing metrics
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH "SUBCOMMAND: rift-cli subscribe"
Event subscription commands
.TP
\fBUsage: rift\-cli subscribe <COMMAND>\fR
.PP
\fBCommands:\fR
.TP
\fBrift\-cli subscribe mach <EVENT>\fR
Subscribe to Mach IPC events
.TP
\fBrift\-cli subscribe cli \-\-event <EVENT> \-\-command <COMMAND> [\-\-args]\fR
Subscribe to events via CLI command execution
.TP
\fBrift\-cli subscribe unsub\-mach <EVENT>\fR
Unsubscribe from Mach IPC events
.TP
\fBrift\-cli subscribe unsub\-cli <EVENT>\fR
Unsubscribe from CLI events
.TP
\fBrift\-cli subscribe list\-cli\fR
List current CLI subscriptions
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH "SUBCOMMAND: rift-cli service"
Manage the launchd service for rift
.TP
\fBUsage: rift\-cli service <COMMAND>\fR
.PP
\fBCommands:\fR
.TP
\fBrift\-cli service install\fR
Install the per\-user launchd service
.TP
\fBrift\-cli service uninstall\fR
Uninstall the per\-user launchd service
.TP
\fBrift\-cli service start\fR
Start (or bootstrap) the service
.TP
\fBrift\-cli service stop\fR
Stop (or bootout/kill) the service
.TP
\fBrift\-cli service restart\fR
Restart the service (kickstart \-k)
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH "SUBCOMMAND: rift-cli verify"
.TP
\fBUsage: rift\-cli verify <CONFIG_PATH>\fR
.TP
\fB<CONFIG_PATH>\fR
 [required]
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.IP RUST_LOG
Tracing/log filter (tracing\-subscriber EnvFilter syntax, e.g. "rift_wm=debug" or "info,rift_wm::actor=trace").
.IP RUST_BACKTRACE
Standard Rust backtrace control. rift forces this to "1" if unset.
.IP RIFT_BS_NAME
Mach bootstrap name used for the rift IPC server. Override only when running multiple rift instances side\-by\-side.
.IP RIFT_CLI_PRETTY
If set to anything other than "0", rift\-cli pretty\-prints JSON output. Defaults to compact output.
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.IP 0
Successful program execution.
.IP 1
Unsuccessful program execution.
.IP 101
The program panicked.
